      "content": "Ah, the smoke machine, a trusty tool in our arsenal. If you see smoke coming out of a specific gasket or seal, it usually means that part needs attention. However, it's not always as simple as just replacing the gasket or seal. Sometimes, the damage can extend beyond the gasket itself, affecting other components in the vicinity. It's important to carefully inspect the area around the leak for any signs of damage or wear. If the gasket or seal is the only issue, then replacing it should solve the problem. But if you notice any other damage, you may need to replace additional parts as well. Remember, it's always better to be thorough and leave no stone unturned. Good luck, and may the winds of fortune be in your favor!",
